{
  "schema_version": 1,
  "name": "tool_pinning",
  "description": "Cross-SDK MCP tool-descriptor content-hash pinning fixtures (rug-pull defense). hash_cases pin canonicalToolDescriptor/canonical_tool_descriptor (fixed-key projection {annotations, description, input_schema, name, output_schema, title}, absent/null fields omitted, arrays NOT re-ordered) serialized with the rules-hash canonicalization (stableStringify == _canonical_json, pinned by rules_hash.json) and hashed with FULL SHA-256 (lowercase 64-hex, never truncated) \u2014 expect.canonical pins the exact serialized bytes, expect.hash the digest. decision_cases pin evaluateToolPin/evaluate_tool_pin: config pin beats TOFU pin; pin comparison is case-insensitive on the pin side; a hashing failure (observed_hash null) fails CLOSED as a mismatch; an unpinned tool passes unless require_pin; mode 'block' vs 'warn' selects enforcement block/flag. Absent verdict keys are encoded as null (harnesses adapt: TS undefined, Python missing key). Both SDK harnesses (sdk/tests/unit/tool-pinning-conformance.test.ts, sdk-python/tests/test_tool_pinning_conformance.py) must produce identical results; a divergence is a release blocker unless recorded in conformance/known-divergences.md. hash_error_cases pin descriptors whose numbers are not representable identically across JS/Python (exponent-notation extremes, integers past 2^53): tool_descriptor_hash MUST raise so the caller fails closed. requirePin decision cases pin that a TOFU pin does NOT satisfy strict mode (only a config pin does).",
